1
00:00:11,033 --> 00:00:12,867
<i> Where's Emma?</i>

2
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,500
<i> No matter what you ask me,</i>

3
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:16,933
<i>I can't answer
because I really don't know!</i>

4
00:00:17,067 --> 00:00:18,567
<i> Don't!</i>

5
00:00:18,700 --> 00:00:20,133
<i> What do you need from me?</i>

6
00:00:20,267 --> 00:00:22,600
<i>I just want to make sure
you're safe.</i>

7
00:00:22,733 --> 00:00:26,200
<i>Please forgive me, Ligaya.
I made your life a hell.</i>

8
00:00:26,333 --> 00:00:27,833
<i> Mookie!</i>

9
00:00:27,967 --> 00:00:30,700
<i>She seems to be getting crazy.
She's like Ma'am Olive.</i>

10
00:00:30,833 --> 00:00:32,633
<i>If you had become
a responsible father,</i>

11
00:00:32,767 --> 00:00:34,600
<i>my family would've been doing
well now.</i>

12
00:00:34,767 --> 00:00:36,267
<i>Look where the body
was recovered.</i>

13
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:38,567
<i>Darn it!
That's Emma's fake grave!</i>

14
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:40,167
<i> Jade already knows I'm alive?</i>

15
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:42,433
<i> Flor! Did Mookie call you?</i>

16
00:00:42,567 --> 00:00:44,800
<i> She told me she would go out.</i>

17
00:00:44,933 --> 00:00:47,467
<i> Emma. It has to be her.</i>

18
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:49,500
<i>She's getting everyone
one by one.</i>

19
00:00:49,633 --> 00:00:51,133
<i> First, it was Ligaya.</i>

20
00:00:51,267 --> 00:00:53,167
<i> And now, Mookie?</i>

21
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:56,733
<i> No. No.</i>

22
00:00:56,867 --> 00:00:58,967
<i> No way in hell.</i>

23
00:01:38,067 --> 00:01:38,933
- Flor!
- Emma!

24
00:01:39,067 --> 00:01:40,067
Emma!

25
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:41,333
Emma!

26
00:01:44,267 --> 00:01:45,200
Thank you, Lord.

27
00:01:45,333 --> 00:01:46,733
You're safe.

28
00:01:46,867 --> 00:01:49,267
I got nervous when I heard
the news from you.

29
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:52,000
Sorry, you almost got harmed
because of my plans.

30
00:01:52,133 --> 00:01:53,333
It's okay.

31
00:01:53,467 --> 00:01:54,333
I'm okay.

32
00:01:54,467 --> 00:01:57,300
Jade failed to kill me.

33
00:01:57,433 --> 00:01:59,033
Just a close call.

34
00:01:59,167 --> 00:02:01,567
Don't go back there, okay?

35
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:02,667
Too bad.

36
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:05,967
I wanted to witness her crazy
moments.

37
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:07,200
Wait.

38
00:02:07,333 --> 00:02:08,867
Where are you going?

39
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,733
I'm going to get Mookie.

40
00:02:10,867 --> 00:02:12,233
What?

41
00:02:12,367 --> 00:02:14,433
You forbid me to go back,
and now you're going there?

42
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:17,467
Jade had killed someone before.

43
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:21,233
Now that she knows I'm alive,
she'll pick on Mookie.

44
00:02:21,367 --> 00:02:23,633
I need to ensure
my child's safety.

45
00:02:23,767 --> 00:02:26,633
Okay. I'll go with you.

46
00:02:26,767 --> 00:02:28,367
-Come on, let's hurry.
- Let's go.

47
00:02:35,967 --> 00:02:37,633
Flor, do you see Mookie?

48
00:02:37,767 --> 00:02:39,167
I haven't seen her yet.

49
00:02:44,967 --> 00:02:46,133
- Why?
- Jade's here.

50
00:02:46,267 --> 00:02:47,933
Maybe Mookie has a date
with her friends.

51
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:49,233
No.

52
00:02:49,367 --> 00:02:51,900
I know all her activities.

53
00:02:52,033 --> 00:02:52,967
I'm her mom.

54
00:02:53,100 --> 00:02:55,233
And she always asks permission
from me.

55
00:02:55,367 --> 00:02:57,200
Why didn't she tell me
she'd go out

56
00:02:57,333 --> 00:02:58,533
if she wasn't meeting with Emma?

57
00:02:59,967 --> 00:03:01,767
Maybe you're only overthinking.

58
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:05,100
Quiet.

59
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:08,133
What?

60
00:03:09,567 --> 00:03:10,867
I can hear her.

61
00:03:12,033 --> 00:03:12,700
Who?

62
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,333
Emma.

63
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:19,433
She's here.

64
00:03:22,867 --> 00:03:25,733
Jade, everyone here is talking.

65
00:03:25,867 --> 00:03:27,333
How come you hear Emma?

66
00:03:31,167 --> 00:03:32,667
What is she listening to?

67
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:33,500
The wind?

68
00:03:34,733 --> 00:03:37,533
Get closer to her.
Haunt her so she gets crazier.

69
00:03:37,667 --> 00:03:39,300
Flor, I can't do that,

70
00:03:39,433 --> 00:03:41,500
especially now that she knows
I'm alive.

71
00:03:41,633 --> 00:03:43,200
I need to be careful.

72
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,400
I knew it!

73
00:03:49,900 --> 00:03:53,233
- I told you, Emma's here.
- Jade!

74
00:03:55,467 --> 00:03:57,233
- Let me go! That's Emma!
- What's wrong with you?

75
00:03:57,367 --> 00:04:00,467
She's a teacher!
That's not Emma!

76
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:01,800
Stop!

77
00:04:11,467 --> 00:04:12,500
There's Mookie.

78
00:04:12,633 --> 00:04:15,167
Mookie, relax.

79
00:04:16,467 --> 00:04:17,567
How, Zayn?

80
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:20,267
I'll see your mom again.

81
00:04:20,400 --> 00:04:22,100
I'm so nervous.

82
00:04:22,233 --> 00:04:24,367
I hope your mom likes me.

83
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:28,067
What if she doesn't come
to like me?

84
00:04:28,233 --> 00:04:31,700
You might end up fighting.

85
00:04:31,833 --> 00:04:33,800
You might get upset
with each other.

86
00:04:33,933 --> 00:04:38,000
I know how important mothers
are in our lives.

87
00:04:38,133 --> 00:04:43,067
And I also know how it feels
not to get along with your mom.

88
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:45,133
Just like my relationship
with Mommy Emma.

89
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:48,500
Just be yourself, okay?

90
00:04:48,633 --> 00:04:49,967
You don't need to impress her.

91
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:51,000
You're not like that.

92
00:04:52,033 --> 00:04:53,833
Just act natural.

93
00:04:53,967 --> 00:04:57,667
Mom will surely love you
as I did.

94
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:59,933
I like you for who you are.

95
00:05:00,067 --> 00:05:01,333
For what you are.

96
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:02,933
Really?

97
00:05:03,067 --> 00:05:06,500
Do you really think your mom
will like me?

98
00:05:07,567 --> 00:05:09,100
I know she will.

99
00:05:09,233 --> 00:05:11,833
I told her everything about us.

100
00:05:11,967 --> 00:05:13,600
How we met...

101
00:05:13,733 --> 00:05:14,900
how we became friends...

102
00:05:15,033 --> 00:05:16,533
our fights.

103
00:05:16,667 --> 00:05:18,733
And now we're exclusive.

104
00:05:18,867 --> 00:05:20,367
She understands.

105
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:22,667
And she got excited
to know you better.

106
00:05:32,033 --> 00:05:32,933
Mommy!

107
00:05:34,833 --> 00:05:36,267
Zayn!

108
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:37,233
Mom.

109
00:05:38,700 --> 00:05:40,400
Hi, Auntie.

110
00:05:42,167 --> 00:05:45,667
I am so sorry about what
happened last time.

111
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:49,300
- Zayn scolded me.
- Mom.

112
00:05:49,433 --> 00:05:51,033
That's Zayn's mom?

113
00:05:52,267 --> 00:05:53,500
Are they dating?

114
00:05:54,700 --> 00:05:57,133
Looks like Zayn will
introduce Mookie.

115
00:05:58,433 --> 00:06:00,100
I'm kidding.

116
00:06:00,233 --> 00:06:02,667
He told me a lot of good things
about you.

117
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:05,667
That's why I requested
that we go out for dinner.

118
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:07,467
So I can get to know you better.

119
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,500
And you get to know me
better, too.

120
00:06:09,667 --> 00:06:11,200
Really?

121
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:12,333
Of course.

122
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:14,733
Let's go.

123
00:06:18,667 --> 00:06:20,833
- Jade!
- Move!

124
00:06:20,967 --> 00:06:22,767
You can never take my daughter
away from me!

125
00:06:22,900 --> 00:06:23,767
- Auntie Jade!
- Auntie Jade!

126
00:06:23,900 --> 00:06:26,433
Darn you, Emma!
You can't take Mookie!

127
00:06:26,733 --> 00:06:28,200
- Auntie Jade!
- Darn you, Emma!

128
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:31,167
You can't take Mookie from me!

129
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:32,700
Let me go! Stop!

130
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:34,400
How dare you!

131
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:38,400
I spent a lot of time
fixing my hair.

132
00:06:38,533 --> 00:06:39,933
And you're just going ruin it?

133
00:06:41,667 --> 00:06:42,833
Who are you?

134
00:06:42,967 --> 00:06:44,700
You attacked me!

135
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:47,100
And now you're asking who I am?

136
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:50,233
Are you high or something?

137
00:06:50,367 --> 00:06:52,200
You. Who are you?

138
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:57,967
I'm sorry.

139
00:06:58,100 --> 00:07:00,333
She's my Aunt.

140
00:07:00,467 --> 00:07:02,633
She's like my mom, too.

141
00:07:02,767 --> 00:07:03,733
What?

142
00:07:06,033 --> 00:07:07,233
This crazy woman?

143
00:07:08,267 --> 00:07:09,833
You're related to her?

144
00:07:12,767 --> 00:07:14,967
I am so, so sorry.

145
00:07:15,133 --> 00:07:17,767
I thought you were somebody
I knew.

146
00:07:17,900 --> 00:07:20,300
I'm really so sorry.

147
00:07:20,433 --> 00:07:21,667
I'm so, so sorry.

148
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:23,133
Zayn?

149
00:07:25,867 --> 00:07:27,600
What kind of people are these?

150
00:07:30,767 --> 00:07:32,233
I'm sorry.

151
00:07:33,767 --> 00:07:37,367
I can never accept this girl
for you.

152
00:07:40,667 --> 00:07:41,667
- Wait.
- Mom.

153
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,367
I'm really sorry...

154
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:45,400
Go, Zayn.

155
00:07:45,533 --> 00:07:46,767
We'll talk about this, okay?

156
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:48,967
- Please excuse me.
- Mookie.

157
00:07:49,133 --> 00:07:50,133
Mookie.

158
00:07:50,267 --> 00:07:51,867
Mookie, baby girl.

159
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,400
I'm so sorry.

160
00:07:53,533 --> 00:07:54,633
Emma.

161
00:07:54,767 --> 00:07:57,000
This is your chance.
Get close to them.

162
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:00,367
Flor, I can't.

163
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:03,600
It might confuse Mookie
even more.

164
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:09,267
Come on, Auntie.

165
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:13,533
That was my chance to change the
impression of Zayn's mom on me.

166
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:21,267
I tried so hard to get Zayn's
mom to like me.

167
00:08:21,433 --> 00:08:24,033
But you ruined everything.

168
00:08:26,067 --> 00:08:26,933
I'm so sorry.

169
00:08:27,067 --> 00:08:32,400
I really want
to understand you, Auntie.

170
00:08:32,533 --> 00:08:34,567
I really want to.

171
00:08:37,233 --> 00:08:39,833
But you became like Mommy Olive.

172
00:08:42,233 --> 00:08:43,133
I think...

173
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,433
you need to seek
professional help.

174
00:08:47,667 --> 00:08:48,533
Mookie.

175
00:08:48,667 --> 00:08:50,067
Mookie.

176
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:52,767
Jade, let her be for now.
Give her space.

177
00:09:03,667 --> 00:09:05,600
This is all Emma's fault.

178
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:08,300
<i> Of course, it is.</i>

179
00:09:08,433 --> 00:09:09,667
<i> Who else?</i>

180
00:09:10,733 --> 00:09:11,967
Shut up!

181
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,500
I didn't say anything.

182
00:09:16,167 --> 00:09:18,133
I'm not talking to you!

183
00:09:24,267 --> 00:09:26,167
I need to get Emma.

184
00:09:28,133 --> 00:09:31,400
I need to find her
and finish her.

185
00:09:31,533 --> 00:09:34,067
I need to kill her
like I did to Altair.

186
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:36,500
How? She's elusive.

187
00:09:36,633 --> 00:09:39,333
You don't have any clue
where to find her.

188
00:09:42,633 --> 00:09:45,067
Why haven't I thought of it?

189
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:51,767
I know what to do, Leticia.

190
00:09:51,900 --> 00:09:54,300
I don't need to find Emma.

191
00:09:55,367 --> 00:09:59,033
Because she will willingly
come out of her burrow.

192
00:10:03,267 --> 00:10:09,733
What does a chicken do
when it sees a snake

193
00:10:09,867 --> 00:10:12,267
lurking around its chick?

194
00:10:29,267 --> 00:10:30,767
Yes, Zayn.

195
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:32,033
I'm already here.

196
00:10:45,167 --> 00:10:47,200
Ma'am Maristela.

197
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:49,067
Let's skip the niceties.

198
00:10:50,167 --> 00:10:51,500
I already know everything.

199
00:10:53,367 --> 00:10:55,100
When I need to know the truth,

200
00:10:56,567 --> 00:10:58,133
I don't chase rumors.

201
00:10:59,267 --> 00:11:01,667
I call my legal team.
It's faster that way.

202
00:11:06,567 --> 00:11:07,633
<i> Is it true?</i>

203
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:10,400
<i>Olive Caparas stole Emma
Joseco's child,</i>

204
00:11:10,533 --> 00:11:15,967
<i>the woman whom she recently
accused of theft.</i>

205
00:11:16,433 --> 00:11:18,833
Your family is full of drama.

206
00:11:18,967 --> 00:11:22,267
A mother who was
institutionalized.

207
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:25,100
A sister who stole her baby

208
00:11:26,067 --> 00:11:28,933
and raised it in a household
of lies.

209
00:11:30,567 --> 00:11:31,867
And you,

210
00:11:33,367 --> 00:11:38,100
caught in the middle
of a public, low-class circus.

211
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:40,267
What else?

212
00:11:43,633 --> 00:11:44,633
Your aunt.

213
00:11:46,433 --> 00:11:49,667
The twin sister of the woman
who stole you.

214
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:56,467
The unhinged creature who
had the nerve to attack me.

215
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:04,567
And now, she's the fiancée
of your father.

216
00:12:06,367 --> 00:12:07,967
Is she the same person
who kidnapped you?

217
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:11,700
Or is it the twin sister?

218
00:12:12,667 --> 00:12:14,767
I can't follow anymore.

219
00:12:14,933 --> 00:12:17,933
I don't care, anyway.

220
00:12:18,067 --> 00:12:19,300
The bottom line is...

221
00:12:20,867 --> 00:12:22,933
I don't want Zayn
to get involved

222
00:12:23,067 --> 00:12:25,500
in a mentally unwell family.

223
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:36,200
I'm not here to offer you money
to stay away from Zayn.

224
00:12:36,333 --> 00:12:38,200
I'm not like that.

225
00:12:38,333 --> 00:12:39,667
This isn't a soap opera.

226
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:45,233
I'm here to give you advice.

227
00:12:45,367 --> 00:12:49,433
Make sure to carefully consider
your decisions in life, okay?

228
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:53,867
Mental instability runs
in your bloodline.

229
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:57,400
You grew up deranged.

230
00:12:57,533 --> 00:12:59,633
The woman who raised you...

231
00:12:59,767 --> 00:13:02,200
You were raised by
a woman who was...

232
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,700
How do I describe it?

233
00:13:08,300 --> 00:13:10,500
Unfit to be a mother.

234
00:13:14,567 --> 00:13:18,300
<i>No matter what I do to you,
you will never change.</i>

235
00:13:18,433 --> 00:13:22,267
<i>So, your horns must be cut off.</i>

236
00:13:27,767 --> 00:13:30,000
<i>No one will hear
your screams anymore.</i>

237
00:13:30,133 --> 00:13:37,800
<i>Now, I can be sure that you'll
never leave me again.</i>

238
00:13:37,933 --> 00:13:41,967
<i>You will be like a living doll.</i>

239
00:13:43,233 --> 00:13:48,433
<i> My living doll.</i>

240
00:13:48,567 --> 00:13:50,533
I'm a mother, Mookie.

241
00:13:50,667 --> 00:13:52,933
A sensible mother.

242
00:13:53,067 --> 00:13:55,233
I'm trained to sense danger.

243
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:57,767
And you?

244
00:13:57,900 --> 00:14:00,767
You are a risk I refuse to take.

245
00:14:02,333 --> 00:14:08,200
What if you suddenly snap
and hurt Zayn?

246
00:14:08,333 --> 00:14:10,700
Have you thought of that?

247
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:12,133
I'm sorry.

248
00:14:13,567 --> 00:14:15,633
But I don't have
a mental illness.

249
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:20,767
With your family's history,
how can you be so sure?

250
00:14:21,933 --> 00:14:26,833
You will stay away
from my son if you love him.

251
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:44,633
Mom!

252
00:14:44,767 --> 00:14:45,800
You're here.

253
00:14:50,700 --> 00:14:54,767
I'm waiting for your Aunt Lorie
because the coffee here is good.

254
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:55,933
Yeah.

255
00:14:56,067 --> 00:14:57,133
Is this yours?

256
00:14:57,267 --> 00:14:58,167
Yes.

257
00:15:00,533 --> 00:15:02,300
Did you see Mookie?

258
00:15:02,467 --> 00:15:03,500
Who?

259
00:15:03,633 --> 00:15:04,633
Mookie.

260
00:15:04,767 --> 00:15:06,967
- Mookie? No, no.
- Yes.

261
00:15:08,367 --> 00:15:09,667
Have you eaten yet?

262
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:11,400
- Yes.
- Are you sure?

263
00:15:39,700 --> 00:15:40,700
Let's eat.

264
00:15:44,033 --> 00:15:46,067
This is the first time
you've served me like this.

265
00:15:51,167 --> 00:15:53,367
I hope it's not too late
to make it up to you.

266
00:15:57,300 --> 00:15:59,533
When will we go and see Danilo?

267
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,067
Maybe not him for now.

268
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,567
Let's meet my friends first.

269
00:16:12,367 --> 00:16:15,267
It's dangerous if I go straight
to my son-in-law.

270
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,333
Let's not see him for now.

271
00:16:19,467 --> 00:16:21,667
Someone might be looking for me.

272
00:16:23,300 --> 00:16:25,700
Besides, I want to focus
on getting my strength back.

273
00:16:27,300 --> 00:16:28,900
Ligaya.

274
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:37,633
Once we resolved the problem
with our child...

275
00:16:43,633 --> 00:16:49,400
I want our family to reunite.

276
00:16:57,567 --> 00:16:59,000
No, Ador.

277
00:17:01,933 --> 00:17:02,933
Why?

278
00:17:06,367 --> 00:17:08,833
My love for you
has long been gone.

279
00:17:14,067 --> 00:17:24,033
From then until now,
you're still the one I love.

280
00:17:31,367 --> 00:17:35,667
I want to pursue you again.

281
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,133
No, Ador.

282
00:17:38,967 --> 00:17:40,500
I can't do that anymore.

283
00:17:44,433 --> 00:17:45,567
Why, Ligaya?

284
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:48,967
Am I no longer worth loving?

285
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:32,133
<i> Your family is full of drama.</i>

286
00:18:33,567 --> 00:18:37,800
<i>Mental instability runs
in your bloodline.</i>

287
00:18:37,933 --> 00:18:41,333
<i> You grew up deranged.</i>

288
00:18:41,467 --> 00:18:43,433
<i> The one who raised you...</i>

289
00:18:43,567 --> 00:18:46,467
<i>You were raised by a woman
who was...</i>

290
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:48,833
<i> unfit to be a mother.</i>

291
00:18:48,967 --> 00:18:51,567
<i>You are a risk I refuse to take.</i>

292
00:18:53,067 --> 00:18:59,100
<i>What if you suddenly snap
and hurt Zayn?</i>

293
00:18:59,267 --> 00:19:01,133
<i> Have you thought of that?</i>

294
00:19:01,267 --> 00:19:03,033
<i> Please stop.</i>

295
00:19:03,167 --> 00:19:05,667
<i> I only want you to accept me.</i>

296
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:07,833
<i> I'd been a good daughter</i>

297
00:19:07,967 --> 00:19:10,367
<i>to Mommy Olive even though
she was hurting me.</i>

298
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:14,500
<i>I loved Mommy Emma even
though she left me.</i>

299
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:29,133
<i> When I was young,</i>

300
00:19:30,267 --> 00:19:34,167
<i>I pretended to be brave despite
being scared.</i>

301
00:19:34,300 --> 00:19:35,400
<i> Why?</i>

302
00:19:36,733 --> 00:19:41,533
<i>No one else would help me aside
from myself.</i>

303
00:19:41,667 --> 00:19:43,667
<i>That's what I also want you
to learn.</i>

304
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,767
<i> I want you to be brave.</i>

305
00:19:45,900 --> 00:19:52,100
<i>Because I won't always come
to your rescue.</i>

306
00:19:52,233 --> 00:19:57,500
<i>I know it's not easy,
but you have to be brave.</i>

307
00:19:57,633 --> 00:20:00,600
<i> I'm still upset with you, Mom.</i>

308
00:20:00,733 --> 00:20:04,000
<i>But I keep returning
to the times</i>

309
00:20:04,167 --> 00:20:06,867
<i>when you supported me
during my struggles.</i>

310
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:12,300
<i>And I still hope and pray
that you'll come to be with me.</i>

311
00:20:12,433 --> 00:20:16,533
<i>To encourage me and reassure me
that you still love me.</i>

312
00:20:16,667 --> 00:20:19,000
<i>I wish you were still here, Mom.</i>

313
00:20:19,133 --> 00:20:23,533
<i>I wish you would hug me,
even just for a moment.</i>

314
00:20:29,767 --> 00:20:32,700
Emma, let's go.
That's enough. Let's go.

315
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:34,900
Mookie's been crying
for days now.

316
00:20:35,967 --> 00:20:38,000
I can't bear
seeing her like that.

317
00:20:38,133 --> 00:20:39,900
Emma, control yourself.

318
00:20:40,700 --> 00:20:44,567
Remember that Boss Logan
let you see Mookie

319
00:20:44,867 --> 00:20:48,833
because you promised
you wouldn't expose yourself.

320
00:20:50,233 --> 00:20:52,333
Marco, my daughter needs me!

321
00:20:53,567 --> 00:20:55,667
Emma, it's more important
to remove the obstacle.

322
00:20:56,033 --> 00:20:56,767
And that's Jade!

323
00:20:57,300 --> 00:21:01,233
If I have to kidnap
my own daughter, I will.

324
00:21:01,367 --> 00:21:03,900
Emma, be a little more patient!

325
00:21:05,867 --> 00:21:07,833
It's easy for you to say

326
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,567
that because
you don't have a child.

327
00:21:10,367 --> 00:21:13,433
You don't experience every day
as if your heart

328
00:21:13,567 --> 00:21:16,000
is being stabbed because
you see your child hurting.

329
00:21:17,233 --> 00:21:20,200
My child and had been separated
for 17 years.

330
00:21:20,333 --> 00:21:23,033
And it had been less than
a year when we separated again.

331
00:21:23,367 --> 00:21:25,167
Do you know how painful it is?

332
00:21:26,700 --> 00:21:28,700
I'm longing
for my daughter's embrace.

333
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:36,433
Emma, I understand you
because I'm also a mother.

334
00:21:36,567 --> 00:21:41,100
If you like to follow Mookie,
go ahead.

335
00:21:41,667 --> 00:21:43,900
We'll wait for you
in the car, okay?

336
00:21:54,467 --> 00:21:56,733
<i>Why am I still
looking for you, Mom?</i>

337
00:21:56,867 --> 00:22:01,567
<i>Why am I still expecting
we'll meet one day?</i>

338
00:22:01,933 --> 00:22:02,900
<i> I've had enough.</i>

339
00:22:03,667 --> 00:22:05,767
<i> I'm waiting for nothing.</i>

340
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:14,367
Come and get your baby chick,
Mother Hen.

341
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:19,000
Tick-tock, be quick before
I count to ten.

342
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:27,067
We've only been together
for a short while,

343
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:29,267
and you're already raising
your voice at me again?

344
00:22:30,733 --> 00:22:32,600
You still haven't changed.

345
00:22:35,967 --> 00:22:40,667
Because you don't want
to believe me.

346
00:22:43,333 --> 00:22:48,600
What do you want me to do
to trust me again?

347
00:22:48,767 --> 00:22:52,067
- I've changed!
- I don't believe you!

348
00:22:53,567 --> 00:22:55,767
I can read you.

349
00:22:55,900 --> 00:22:57,767
You're still a monster.

350
00:22:57,900 --> 00:23:00,567
You will never change.

351
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:05,200
I'm trying to change
so that when we finally meet,

352
00:23:06,533 --> 00:23:11,033
we can be together.

353
00:23:11,167 --> 00:23:14,367
But why are you doing this
to me?

354
00:23:14,500 --> 00:23:15,500
Why?

355
00:23:15,633 --> 00:23:18,867
Why? What did you do to me?

356
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:21,700
You made my life miserable.

357
00:23:22,900 --> 00:23:25,767
I gave away our children

358
00:23:25,900 --> 00:23:29,633
because I was scared
that you'd hurt them, too.

359
00:23:29,900 --> 00:23:33,500
But you can never ruin
my life again.

360
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:37,767
Do you think I'll yield
to you again?

361
00:23:37,900 --> 00:23:38,967
No way!

362
00:23:40,100 --> 00:23:41,933
If you've looked for me
for a long time,

363
00:23:42,067 --> 00:23:44,867
I, on the other hand, have long
trained myself to fight,

364
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:47,033
especially against people
like you!

365
00:23:47,167 --> 00:23:48,267
You're worthless.

366
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:49,733
You're an irresponsible husband.

367
00:23:49,867 --> 00:23:53,667
You're an irresponsible father.
I don't like all of this.

368
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:15,667
Believe me...

369
00:24:43,633 --> 00:24:45,667
<i> Happy birthday, Mom!</i>

370
00:24:47,100 --> 00:24:49,900
<i>I'm just right here.
I'll be with you.</i>

371
00:25:04,433 --> 00:25:06,533
There you are, Emma.

372
00:25:06,667 --> 00:25:09,700
You've finally come out
of your burrow

373
00:25:09,833 --> 00:25:12,700
in all your pathetic glory.

374
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:16,233
You're so real now.

375
00:25:16,367 --> 00:25:19,267
You're no longer a ghost
or imagination.

376
00:25:19,767 --> 00:25:22,000
I can finally ruin you.

377
00:25:22,133 --> 00:25:24,567
<i> Kill her.</i>

378
00:25:24,700 --> 00:25:26,267
<i> Kill her.</i>

379
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:28,200
You bet I will.

380
00:25:28,333 --> 00:25:34,900
I'll make sure that this will be
your last day, Emma.

381
00:25:35,033 --> 00:25:36,667
Goodbye.

382
00:25:41,167 --> 00:25:45,467
Zayn, I've thought
about it already.

383
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:47,200
I'm done with this.

384
00:25:47,333 --> 00:25:48,400
No.

385
00:25:48,533 --> 00:25:52,133
So, it's because of you.
It all came from you.

386
00:25:52,267 --> 00:25:55,967
You're the reason why my child
became a monster.

387
00:25:56,100 --> 00:25:59,367
Is this the drug you're taking?

388
00:25:59,500 --> 00:26:01,433
This is not Pryvaxil.

389
00:26:01,567 --> 00:26:02,600
What?

390
00:26:02,733 --> 00:26:04,833
Jade, someone tampered
with your medicine.

391
00:26:04,967 --> 00:26:06,567
Remember, Emma.

392
00:26:06,700 --> 00:26:08,667
No one will replace Jade's
medication anymore.

393
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:10,733
Once she takes the Pryvaxil,

394
00:26:10,900 --> 00:26:12,433
she will return to her senses

395
00:26:12,567 --> 00:26:16,267
and make sure you can't take
Mookie back.

396
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:18,267
I will show myself to her.

397
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:19,800
To her and Danilo.

398
00:26:19,933 --> 00:26:23,667
I will give her the war
that will take her down

399
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:26,300
and put her where she belongs.

400
00:26:26,433 --> 00:26:28,433
In hell.

401
00:26:28,567 --> 00:26:30,833
You want a bloody fight?

402
00:26:32,833 --> 00:26:36,833
I will give you a bloodbath.
